# PostgreSQL MCP Server Settings
# Use this file to configure the PostgreSQL MCP server for Claude Desktop
#
# Format:
# SETTING_NAME=value
#
# Required Settings:
# -----------------
# POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING - PostgreSQL connection string
#   Format: postgresql://[user[:password]@][host][:port][/dbname]
#   Example: postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/mydb
#
# Optional Settings:
# -----------------
# CONTAINER_NAME - Name of the Docker container (default: postgres-mcp-server)
# DOCKER_IMAGE - Docker image name and tag (default: mcp/postgres:latest)
# RESTART_CLAUDE - Whether to restart Claude Desktop if it's running (true/false, default: true)
#
# Examples:
# POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/mydb
# CONTAINER_NAME=my-postgres-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/postgres:custom
# RESTART_CLAUDE=false
#
# Default settings (uncomment and modify as needed):
POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING=postgresql://localhost:5432/mydb
# CONTAINER_NAME=postgres-mcp-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/postgres:latest
# RESTART_CLAUDE=true
